      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a vital constitutional safeguard that protects fundamental individual rights from government overreach, regardless of how the law is technically structured. It allows courts to strike down laws that infringe upon deeply rooted liberties, such as privacy and bodily autonomy, which the majority often ignores. This doctrine has been instrumental in expanding civil rights by ensuring the government cannot arbitrarily trample on personal freedoms.",
      "source": "target",
